data.description: Quaint 1959 single family 3 BR/2 BA home featuring original hardwood floors, large picture windows and oozing with original charm. The kitchen overlooks Johnson Ave with an adjacent dining area located between the living room and family room. Sliding glass doors in the family room bring in an abundance of natural light and open up to a deck and private backyard with views of the surrounding hills. The bedrooms are on either side of a hallway accessed from the living room featuring a fireplace. This approximately 1480 sq ft house sits on a 6000 sq ft lot higher up from the street with mature landscaping. There is also privacy in the front and nice views of the hills from the front porch. The oversized two car garage provides a laundry area and ample room for storage. There is plenty of room for additional parking in the driveway. This house has a great location close to downtown San Luis Obispo, Sinsheimer Elementary School and San Luis Obispo High School. There is a Smart & Final grocery store close by on Johnson Ave and easy access to hiking and biking trails. Don't miss this opportunity to own a home on the Central Coast in beautiful San Luis Obispo.
